Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.57,0:02:21.20,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(330,580)\bord0.5\shad1.5\b1\fnArial\blur0.3\fax-0.15\3c&H5B5B5B&\t(4050,4620,\blur5)\pos(499.455,302)}The Shocking New\NMFG Generation
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.25,0:02:18.49,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And he's off!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.29,0:02:22.65,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,An entirely AI-controlled drone gives chase,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.81,0:02:27.96,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,beaming back the white-hot MFG footage \Nthat fans around the world expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.43,0:02:31.17,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He hits the incline with \Nthe pedal to the metal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.82,0:02:36.14,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of run will we see from \Nthis challenger from England today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.62,0:02:38.01,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Let's watch and find out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.21,0:02:42.05,Default,Ren Dad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.05,0:02:46.09,Default,Ren Dad,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect him to enter under \Nhis father's family name, Katagiri.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.94,0:02:49.29,Default,Mayuko,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he's trying to send a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.75,0:02:53.98,Default,Mayuko,0000,0000,0000,,He might be reaching out to Ken-chan, \Nwho he hopes is watching somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.62,0:03:01.97,Default,Mayuko,0000,0000,0000,,Telling him "Your son, Kanata, \Nis right here," without outright saying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.48,0:03:09.71,Default,Ren Dad,0000,0000,0000,,He'd really go that far to reach out to the \Nfather who abandoned him and his mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.66,0:03:15.71,Default,Mayuko,0000,0000,0000,,He's the only one who can \Nknow how he really feels.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.71,0:03:20.96,Default,Mayuko,0000,0000,0000,,His mother's passed on, he's left the \Ncountry he lived in with his grandparents,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.96,0:03:23.80,Default,Mayuko,0000,0000,0000,,and he's come to a \Nforeign land all by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.41,0:03:33.44,Default,Mayuko,0000,0000,0000,,Just thinking about how he might \Nbe feeling makes my chest hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.09,0:03:36.61,Default,Mayuko,0000,0000,0000,,It's so sad, I can't bear to watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.13,0:03:41.86,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,It's Ogata. Am I coming through clearly?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.20,0:03:44.12,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Loud and clear, Ogata-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.12,0:03:47.85,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,This is a long course. \NTry to keep your focus. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.23,0:03:49.04,Italics,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.70,0:03:51.54,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,I gotta say, Ogata...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.54,0:03:55.25,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs10\bord1.2\shad0\blur0.3\3c&H2B6C60&\c&H44F2DE&\pos(501.819,73.455)}Qualifying Run
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.93,0:03:55.25,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Number 86? I'm surprised you \Nmanaged to get a two-digit number.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.53,0:03:59.67,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't really think we'd get it \Neither when I put in for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.67,0:04:02.13,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,but luckily for us, it wasn't being used.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.49,0:04:09.22,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Sector 1's looking rough so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.76,0:04:13.14,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno how you expect him to compete \Nin a manual with an H-pattern shifter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.00,0:04:18.68,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Paddle shifters with dual clutch is the \Nstandard now. Anything else is a handicap.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.44,0:04:21.18,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.36,0:04:24.99,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,54th place? You gotta be kidding me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.99,0:04:29.22,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Must be some kind of system error. \NHappens all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.22,0:04:32.17,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way your busted \Nold 86 car could be so high up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.17,0:04:34.46,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Less of the "busted," Shun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.16,0:04:38.67,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,That said, I agree it's probably an error.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.30,0:04:54.46,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Holy crap. It says he's up to 53rd.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.46,0:04:56.40,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,It's not an error. Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.66,0:05:01.11,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,The central computer's \Nstuck an attention flag on the 86.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.11,0:05:05.03,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,No way. That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.03,0:05:06.74,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.74,0:05:09.91,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Car 86 has been marked\Nwith an attention flag.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.36,0:05:14.51,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,From memory, the only other driver \Nto manage that feat in his debut event
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.51,0:05:18.25,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,was Michael Beckenbauer last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.51,0:05:21.97,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The 19-year-old Katagiri Kanata is on a roll!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.47,0:05:29.18,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't make any sense. The top 100...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.18,0:05:34.40,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,hell, the top 200 is full of cars with \Nmore horsepower than Kanata's 86.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.81,0:05:37.39,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,So how is he so high up on the timing charts?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.69,0:05:42.01,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it means Kanata's cornering\N is just that much faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.01,0:05:43.85,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that simple, Ogata.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.85,0:05:49.70,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,No, it can't be that. The grip-to-weight ratio\N of MFG poses a real issue in that regard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.46,0:05:53.41,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Shaving off a bit of time \Nin corners won't help much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.72,0:05:57.50,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,In Sector 1, sheer grunt is \Nthe only way to get ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:06:00.67,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,You say that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.57,0:06:05.71,Flashback,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,The thing about a uniform\N grip-to-weight ratio is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.96,0:06:08.68,Flashback,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,the heavier the car, the fatter its tires.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.68,0:06:12.62,Flashback,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,This means a mid-engine design and \Nfour-wheel drive are disadvantages.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.62,0:06:17.14,Flashback,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,And sinking money into reducing weight \Nmeans thinner tires, which defeats the object.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.74,0:06:22.33,Flashback,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,There's no limit on engine power, but if \Nyou go too hard, your tires won't hold up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.86,0:06:27.61,Flashback,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Even many of the top teams haven't\N figured out the optimal balance yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.84,0:06:30.97,Flashback,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why European models \Nthat are balanced and powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.97,0:06:33.94,Flashback,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,without needing to be modded\N have come out on top so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.33,0:06:39.12,Flashback,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,But it's also why the rule gets mocked \Nand called the "rich man's regulation."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.12,0:06:43.38,Flashback,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not quite sure that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.74,0:06:45.69,Flashback,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,There has to be another way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.18,0:06:49.89,Flashback,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I have to admit, this is \Nevery bit as exciting as I'd hoped.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.31,0:06:54.26,Flashback,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Grip-to-weight ratio being the only rule...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.83,0:06:57.17,Flashback,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Who could've come up with an idea like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.17,0:07:03.31,Flashback,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Probably MFG's executive organizer.\NSome guy named Ryo Takahashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.33,0:07:09.76,Flashback,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Despite how big MFG has gotten, \Nno one knows how old he is or where he's from.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.08,0:07:14.03,Flashback,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,And he never shows his face.\NHe's a real man of mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.75,0:07:17.80,Flashback,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I think he might be incredibly smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.17,0:07:22.06,Flashback,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,In Japanese, you'd call him\N a "tensai." A genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.03,0:07:26.09,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:32.61,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The 86 car is nearly done with Sector 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.61,0:07:35.39,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He's moved up again and \Nis currently in 52nd place!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.64,0:07:37.85,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,It's all downhill from this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.12,0:07:43.02,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,That means more weight to the front, \Nso adjust your brake balance. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.39,0:07:45.28,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,The switch on panel three, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.28,0:07:46.61,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,That's the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.04,0:07:49.22,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting a bit more used to the car now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.61,0:07:51.15,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try to pick up the pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.45,0:07:54.19,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.19,0:07:56.84,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,So he's been taking it easy up to now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.44,0:08:00.95,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Who the heck is this Kanata kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.95,0:08:02.71,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,What's his past record like?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.16,0:08:07.28,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really know. Someone \NI trust made the introductions...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.84,0:08:10.67,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,And when I met him, \Nhe seemed like a good guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.67,0:08:15.89,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,All I know for sure is he went to \Na famous racing school in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.05,0:08:26.88,Italics,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Fantastic job, Ogata-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.21,0:08:31.62,Italics,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,The balance of the car's underbody \Nis spot-on, brakes included.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.99,0:08:33.45,Italics,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,With this baby...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.96,0:08:36.91,Italics,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I may even be able to do\N what I came here for.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.85,0:08:47.33,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He's broken into the top 50! \NTalk about rapid! He's blazing downhill!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.33,0:08:50.19,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like we're witnessing \Nthe birth of a superstar!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.64,0:08:53.12,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Katagiri Kanata, only 19 years of age!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.12,0:08:55.01,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,Are you kidding me? Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.58,0:08:59.72,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,Get me Maebashi... No, put me through \Nto Ryosuke direct. It's an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.37,0:09:07.44,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Ryosuke. \NAre you watching the race live?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.44,0:09:14.05,Default,Ryosuke,0000,0000,0000,,No. I'm doing a pretty big procedure soon, \Nso I was prepping for that. What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.05,0:09:17.74,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,He's actually here. Fujiwara's student.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.37,0:09:21.91,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,But he entered under the name \NKatagiri instead of Rivington.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.91,0:09:23.94,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe I missed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.94,0:09:27.04,Italics,Ryosuke,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Well, that's good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.32,0:09:30.25,Default,Ryosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your eyes on that driver, Fumihiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.61,0:09:35.67,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the AI's already got \Nan attention flag on him, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.11,0:09:41.69,Default,Ryosuke,0000,0000,0000,,He's got the potential to figure out\Nand overcome the rule I introduced...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.69,0:09:44.41,Default,Ryosuke,0000,0000,0000,,as part of MFG's new generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.68,0:09:47.20,Italics,Ryosuke,0000,0000,0000,,Surgery time. Hanging up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.08,0:09:53.48,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,Curt as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.07,0:09:57.83,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,And what's this stuff about \N"figuring out" the rule, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.16,0:10:00.70,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,You never mentioned that to me before.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.46,0:10:03.61,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,Ryosuke!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.98,0:10:09.00,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Car 86 is climbing the leaderboard\N at an unbelievable rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.00,0:10:11.17,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He's currently 44th.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.17,0:10:16.47,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Once past the large torii gate, the course \Nveers away from the shoreline and back uphill.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.64,0:10:30.35,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Car 86 has dropped down a place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.35,0:10:32.77,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He's losing a bit of speed going uphill.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.77,0:10:37.36,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the Toyota 86 GT has a displacement\N disadvantage next to the competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.82,0:10:42.21,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Once the course passes the highest point \Non the old Route 1, it enters Sector 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.21,0:10:44.53,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And it's no exaggeration \Nto say that the gains
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.53,0:10:48.75,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,made on this stretch are what racing\N on Odawara Pikes Peak is all about!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.13,0:10:52.46,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Ogata-san, I'm gonna try \Nand pick up the pace a bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.73,0:10:55.68,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,That idiot. Gimme the headset, Ogata!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.68,0:10:57.80,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Ow, ow. What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.05,0:11:01.77,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,You're heading into Sector 3.\N Quit screwing around!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.77,0:11:04.51,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, Kanata! Did you forget my advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.51,0:11:08.48,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,If a rookie who doesn't know the course \Nattacks it too hard here, he might die! Over!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.80,0:11:10.69,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}Don't worry, Aiba-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.13,0:11:12.19,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,You see, this course...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.48,0:11:14.40,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,A movie of it is playing in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.71,0:11:19.19,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I need to focus now, so forgive me\N for the radio silence. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.19,0:11:27.45,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And so, he crosses into the steep downhill \Nsection that sends you plunging 864 meters
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.45,0:11:31.12,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,like a meteor toward the finish line.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.35,0:11:34.08,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a challenge for \Nrookie Katagiri Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.08,0:11:39.05,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Will he taste glory or \Nbitter disappointment?
