Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.34,0:11:54.71,Top,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,MF Ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.74,0:11:59.74,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,That dumbass. I'm gonna \Nslug him when he gets back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.00,0:12:03.70,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,That's what happens when you \Ndon't respect your senpai's advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.11,0:12:07.25,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,I get that you've got \Na great driving technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.25,0:12:09.99,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,but a rich kid who \Ngrew up driving on circuits
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.99,0:12:13.17,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,won't understand how scary \Na natural downhill course can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.74,0:12:18.25,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,The stuff they teach you in school is \N{\i1}always{\i0} useless out in the real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.63,0:12:20.34,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you get that, Kanata?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.53,0:12:35.15,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.15,0:12:38.61,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Every time he goes through\Na checkpoint, he gains places.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.45,0:12:43.53,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,This is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.85,0:12:49.87,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it should be expected from \Na student of a legendary downhill racer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.41,0:13:07.26,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,The 86 is moving around like a go-kart. \NIt could spin out at any moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.84,0:13:11.53,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Hell, it's already halfway there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.20,0:13:16.10,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Is he serious about driving on the edge \Nlike this all the way to the finish?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.65,0:13:18.89,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Are you nuts, Kanata?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.48,0:13:24.81,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,I think he might be serious about trying \Nto set a time that gets him into the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.81,0:13:26.78,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,You mean, break into the Godly Fifteen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.58,0:13:32.83,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way. That's completely \Nimpossible. I mean, he's in an 86.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.26,0:13:36.41,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,It's not very likely, \Nbut it's not impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.05,0:13:41.88,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,With that being the case, we'd be \Nbetter off not insisting that he brakes more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.13,0:13:47.55,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,It might even be safer to help him \Nmaintain his crazy motivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.01,0:13:50.84,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,I know more about \Na driver's psychology than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.97,0:13:54.75,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,How's this for a plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.80,0:14:01.11,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,That {\i1}can't{\i0} be a good idea. \NThat's like telling him to go on the attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.11,0:14:04.03,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it. Have faith in Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.56,0:14:05.72,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,That kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.13,0:14:10.70,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno what it is, but his driving \Nis beyond what you can imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.07,0:14:13.29,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,I got the fifth best time, so I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.61,0:14:17.04,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,There's something fundamentally \Ndifferent about where he's at.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.47,0:14:21.00,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, quick. Tell him, Ogata.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.91,0:14:26.08,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Ogata here. Just giving you\N an update. No need to respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:29.68,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,There's 26 cars ahead of you. Over!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.01,0:14:33.56,Italics,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Good job, Ogata-san. \NThat's just what I wanted to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.29,0:14:48.65,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The way he's shot up the leaderboard \Nsince entering Sector 3 is dizzying.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.90,0:14:52.21,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Can this really be \Na rookie in his first race?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.21,0:14:55.87,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,This Katagiri Kanata kid is\N displaying unimaginable potential!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.35,0:15:01.07,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And with a driving style that \Nhas a whiff of danger about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.07,0:15:05.80,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,he approaches Odawara Pikes \NPeak's infamous death zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.76,0:15:12.34,Italics,Seven,0000,0000,0000,,The commentator, Tanaka-san, \Nseems really hyped up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.84,0:15:14.97,Italics,Seven,0000,0000,0000,,There's a real buzz in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.18,0:15:19.87,Italics,Seven,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata's in the mountains of Hakone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.58,0:15:25.81,Italics,Seven,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Kanata, you stupid idiot! \NYou never said anything about racing in MFG.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.53,0:15:31.16,Italics,Seven,0000,0000,0000,,Hakone's mountains are filled with tigers\Nand leopards and crocodiles and bears.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.16,0:15:36.58,Italics,Seven,0000,0000,0000,,There's fearsome beasts around \Nevery corner. It's incredibly dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.58,0:15:40.75,Italics,Seven,0000,0000,0000,,It's no place for a good-natured boy like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.29,0:15:44.04,Italics,Seven,0000,0000,0000,,You're a stupid liar, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.01,0:15:51.14,Italics,Seven,0000,0000,0000,,You told me you came to \NJapan to find your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.95,0:15:58.39,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Cast your eye on this. See how the whole area \Naround old Kawaki-en is shrouded in mist?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.00,0:16:01.85,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since Mount Fuji's north side\N erupted a few years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:05.73,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,depending on the wind, this area can \Nbecome choked with volcanic gases.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.31,0:16:12.90,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Year after year, this abandoned \Nhot springs district is beset by thick fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.18,0:16:17.24,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,You might even say they're clouds \Nof death that wander a ghost town.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.15,0:16:21.31,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And there goes the 86 car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.04,0:16:27.42,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Into the death zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.43,0:16:33.13,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hold on. Is it just me or \Nis the fog even thicker than usual?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.69,0:16:38.00,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Odawara Pikes Peak sees a lot of accidents, \Nand most of them happen around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.37,0:16:42.60,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Even veterans tend to \Nprefer to play it safe here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.54,0:16:57.02,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,He talks a big game about knowing \Nthe course, and so far, he's proved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.75,0:16:59.37,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Visibility might be nil,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.37,0:17:03.97,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,but he has a good idea how far apart the \Ncorners are, and which direction they go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.47,0:17:06.71,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,You can see it by the lines he's taking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.63,0:17:13.03,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,But a 2D map in your head \Nisn't gonna help here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.40,0:17:18.51,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a circuit. A public road \Nhas gaps in the asphalt and dips.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.08,0:17:23.29,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,You could be braking and have \Nthe Gs drop out from under you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.29,0:17:29.23,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,or hit a patch that sends you two meters \Noff-line in a corner. Plenty of spots like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.23,0:17:34.44,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs15\bord1.4\shad0\blur0.3\3c&H387469&\c&H44F2DE&\pos(587,56)}Qualifying Run
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.64,0:17:34.44,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Unless you know what you're dealing with and \Nhow the car will react, you're bound to crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.91,0:17:37.37,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,So how's Kanata pulling this off?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.86,0:17:38.91,Flashback,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,You see, this course...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.61,0:17:41.66,Flashback,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,A movie of it is playing in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.04,0:17:44.11,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,What did he mean by a movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.62,0:17:48.75,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Is he talking about the demo runs \Non the official website?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.73,0:17:50.75,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.16,0:17:54.34,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Odawara Pikes Peak is 40 kilometers long.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.34,0:17:57.60,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,He can't possibly have memorized all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.07,0:18:16.80,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I'm freaking out, Shun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.45,0:18:22.10,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata can't see a thing, and watching him \Ngo into corners at these kind of speeds...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.79,0:18:25.58,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,It's crazy scary. I can barely watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.01,0:18:30.83,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so nervous, \NI'm starting to feel nauseous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.63,0:18:36.01,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, man. I think I really might puke.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.01,0:18:38.01,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Get a grip, Ogata.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.01,0:18:39.34,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,And do your job.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.26,0:18:41.43,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Ogata here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.06,0:18:45.64,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,You have 16 cars left. I repeat, 16 left.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.60,0:18:47.48,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Over!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.28,0:18:55.23,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The 86 car is nearly into \Nthe points-paying positions!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.23,0:18:59.86,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He shows no signs of flinching in the face \Nof the danger presented by the death zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.08,0:19:05.23,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,We're seeing an otherworldly performance\N here from 19-year-old Katagiri Kanata!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.02,0:19:10.03,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,He might actually bag some points.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.60,0:19:13.25,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think that was even possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.25,0:19:15.21,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial\fscx90\blur0.3\fs24\shad0\bord1.4\3c&H13A6C4&\c&H15FFF0&\move(48.727,59.636,48.727,-46.364)}Points\NSystem
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.25,0:19:15.21,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial\fscx90\blur0.3\fs18\shad0\bord1.5\3c&H13A6C4&\c&H15FFF0&\move(70.545,78.545,70.545,-27.455)}Position
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.25,0:19:15.21,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial\fscx90\blur0.3\fs18\shad0\bord1.5\3c&H13A6C4&\c&H15FFF0&\move(233.455,78.545,233.455,-27.455)}Points
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.25,0:19:15.21,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial\fscx90\blur0.3\fs18\shad0\bord1.5\3c&H13A6C4&\c&H15FFF0&\move(403.636,78.545,403.636,-27.455)}Position
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.25,0:19:15.21,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial\fscx90\blur0.3\fs18\shad0\bord1.5\3c&H13A6C4&\c&H15FFF0&\move(553.455,77.818,553.455,-28.182)}Points
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.84,0:19:16.91,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Making the top 30 where \Nthe points are dished out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.91,0:19:21.47,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,is the dream and ambition \Nof every MFG participant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.98,0:19:25.83,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Even scoring a tenth of a point \Ncomes with plenty of benefits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.22,0:19:32.69,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,You get your tires free, and they set you up\N with a booth without you needing to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.29,0:19:37.90,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,But best of all is you get your \Ncar number highlighted in gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.96,0:19:45.20,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,It looks so sweet. Plus, it's a mark of pride \Nfor racers who have scored points.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.20,0:19:47.66,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,That's plenty for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.26,0:19:52.17,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I would never ask to make the Godly Fifteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.76,0:19:55.63,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Just don't do anything \Ncrazy out there, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.12,0:20:01.17,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,You can total the car for all I care.\NJust make it back in one piece,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.52,0:20:04.72,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,and I'll welcome you back with a hug!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.78,0:20:16.98,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Hard on the brakes as the steep \Ndownhill slope leads into a 90 left!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.98,0:20:19.82,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He blazes through the \NMiyanoshita intersection in style!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.44,0:20:21.91,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Would you look at that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.91,0:20:28.53,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The footage from Car 86's drone \Nclearly shows a total lack of visibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.53,0:20:31.32,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It's enough to give you chills.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.32,0:20:35.00,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Yet he's managed to slip past \Neight cars in the death zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.74,0:20:37.71,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,I'm at a loss here, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.71,0:20:43.37,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have the vocabulary to describe \Nwhat the 86 is accomplishing here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.33,0:20:45.71,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,That's 26th place!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.89,0:20:51.47,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,That's 25th!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.06,0:20:55.52,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,This is the kind of thing \Nthat makes MFG a must-watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.81,0:21:01.11,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The arrival of this driver is going \Nto be {\i0}the{\i1} hot topic of this season!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.04,0:21:03.90,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And he's out of the death zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.07,0:21:11.62,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,You can see the Ohiradai hairpin \Nup ahead of the 86 car, clear as day!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.99,0:21:39.33,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting flashbacks. For a second, \NI saw that black-and-white Panda Trueno.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.25,0:21:44.25,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,That's Fujiwara Takumi's \Nsuper high-speed four-wheel drift!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.36,0:21:51.46,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Ogata here! 9 cars left! Over!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.49,0:23:35.10,Italics,Narration,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Turn 03: \NThe Kamaboko Straight.